    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It was found that the `dispose()` calls were a result of changing the \"widget params\".\n\nConsider there's a custom widget called `<ItemsOfSpecificColorFilter specificColor={color}/>`.\nIt filters by `item.color === specificColor`.\n\nSo `itemsOfSpecificColorFilter()` function (in the connector function implementation) receives a `widgetParams` object from which it can read the `specificColor` parameter.\n\nThe weird thing is that whenever `specificColor` property changes, the connector's  `dispose()` function is called, causing the `initialUiState` filter value to be discarded. I.e. it `dispose()`s of the custom filter connector every time any of the connector parameters are changed.\n\nThis type of behavior is not cool and we consider it a bug.",
